limits.h
- contains symbolic constants for data type sizes



float.h
- contains symbolic constants for data type sizes



string.h (strings)
- has the strlen() method that returns the length of a string, excluding the null character




ctype.h (character set functions)
- isdigit(c) - returns 0 or 1 depending on if the character is a digit
- tolower(c) - returns the lower case value of c
